- 2.0.3 | May 17 2026:

  -- New Features --

[New] ipset: --force flag on 'apf ipset update' and '--ipset-update' bypasses
      per-list refresh intervals and IPSET_REFRESH, refreshing every loaded
      set immediately; useful for iterating on ipset.rules or pulling upstream
      list updates ahead of the next cron cycle

  -- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] ipset: per-list log=1 now installs LOG rule independent of global
      LOG_DROP; previously gated on LOG_DROP=1 (default 0), silently
      suppressing per-list logging the user explicitly opted into;
      --ipset-update warns when an entry references a set not yet loaded
      instead of skipping silently (user must run 'apf -s' to install
      newly added entries)
[Fix] CC_LOG, LOG_IA: per-feature LOG opt-ins now install LOG rules
      independent of global LOG_DROP; affects geoip CC_DENY/CC_ALLOW/CC_DENYP
      LOG rules (apf_geoip.sh, 6 sites) and SSH_LOG/TELNET_LOG chains
      (log.rules)
[Fix] validate_config: LOG_LEVEL, LOG_TARGET, and LOG_RATE are now
      validated whenever set (previously gated on LOG_DROP=1); after the
      per-feature LOG decoupling, consumers use these vars even when
      LOG_DROP=0, so invalid LOG_TARGET="BOGUS" silently produced broken
      iptables -j BOGUS rules

  -- Changes --

[Change] LOG_DROP semantic clarified across all surfaces: now governs only
      the end-of-chain default-drop catchall (** IN_TCP DROP ** etc.);
      per-feature LOG opt-ins (CC_LOG, LOG_IA, RAB_LOG_HIT, RAB_LOG_TRIP,
      ipset per-list log) are independent and do not require LOG_DROP=1;
      doc sync in conf.apf, README.md, FLOW.md, apf.8 (new LOG_DROP +
      LOG_IA entries), and apf_validate.sh comment
[Change] RAB_LOG_HIT, RAB_LOG_TRIP: per-feature LOG opt-ins now install
      LOG rules independent of global LOG_DROP; previously OR-gated
      (LOG_DROP=1 force-enabled RAB logging even with per-feature flag
      off) per documentation. Behavior change: operators relying on
      LOG_DROP=1 to force RAB logging must now set RAB_LOG_HIT=1 and/or
      RAB_LOG_TRIP=1 explicitly; affects apf_core.sh:882 (RABTRIP) and
      :915 (RABHIT)
[Change] apf --info dashboard renames "Log drops:" to "Default-drop log:"
      to match the clarified LOG_DROP semantic (end-of-chain catchall only,
      not a global packet-logging master switch)
